div.p:
B. picta. Smith, Eχ. Bot. t. 101;
                    Hook. Ex. Fl. t. 89; Bot. Mag. t.
                    2962; Lodd. Bot. Cab. t. 571.—B. hirta. Wallich.

1. Μ. officinalis; leaves oblongo-elliptical,
                    subacumi-nate, glabrous, paler beneath, nerves simple; peduncles few-flowered;
                    perianth urceolate.

Tribe 1. Sambuceae.Kunth.
                    Corolla regular, rotate, seldom tubular: style none: stigmas three, sessile;
                    raphe on the inner side of the ovule.

Mr Lindley considers this as a connecting link between Resedaceae and Urticeae;
                    Mr Brown, however, thinks that they differ widely. Both the above genera are
                    dioecious.
